    • getCards

      public Queue<ObjectiveCard> getCards(String binFileName)
      Retrieves a Queue of ObjectiveCard objects. If a binary file containing serialized Objective objects exists, it deserializes and returns the Queue from it. If the binary file does not exist, create a new one by call getCardsFromJson()
      Specified by:
      getCards in class AbstractCardFactory<ObjectiveCard>
      Parameters:
      binFileName - the name of the .bin file
      Returns:
      A Queue of ObjectiveCards objects obtained either from existing binary file or serialized from JSON.
      Throws:
      RuntimeException - If an error occurs during file operations or deserialization.

    • deserializeQueue

      public Queue<ObjectiveCard> deserializeQueue(File binFile)
      Deserialize the ObjectiveCard from the .bin file. If the file is corrupted or not up-to-date, it will be deleted and the getCards() method will be called to create a new one
